                <h1>Lois Lowry: The Life and Legacy of a Beloved Author</h1>
                <p>Lois Lowry, an acclaimed American author, was born on March 20, 1937, in Honolulu, Hawaii. She is best known for her children's and young adult literature, including the classic "The Giver," which explores complex themes of memory, identity, and society. Throughout her career, Lowry has won numerous awards, including two Newbery Medals.</p>
